<paragraph blockId="41.[136,1451,337,508]" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,374,400]" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="C. Schweinf." box="[596,766,374,400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="41" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvilabius">
<emphasis box="[596,766,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">M. parvilabius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having lateral sepals connate at the base forming a flat synsepal and falcate petals. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" box="[574,698,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="41" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xiphion">
<emphasis box="[574,698,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">M. xiphion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the caespitose habit 
<emphasis box="[1164,1187,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">vs</emphasis>
. proliferous, yellowish flowers 
<emphasis box="[228,251,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">vs</emphasis>
. purplish and subquadrate base of the petals, trilobed just above the middle and abruptly contracted into a falcate middle lobe 
<emphasis box="[358,381,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="252">vs</emphasis>
. obovate base contracted into a slender falcate apex.
</paragraph>
